            {
               "text": "<h3>Europe: Visigoths</h3>The exact origin of the Goths is uncertain, as they left no early written records. Some scholars suggest they may have originated in what is now Poland. There is also debate on whether the Goths constituted a distinct ethnic group; some researchers believe they may have been a confederation of various tribes",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "e4d4873d-f83a-4e68-845d-446cf7d1d58e",
                     "text": "Mark, J. J.",
                     "page": "Visigoth",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2019",
                        "month": "09",
                        "day": "16"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": "."
            },
            {
               "text": "The Visigoths, also known as the \"Western Goths\",  split from the Ostrogoths in the 4th century. One of the most significant events in their history is the invasion and sack of Rome in <htdate0>, led by their king Alaric I, who died shortly afterward. His successor, Ataulf, expanded Visigothic influence, conquering parts of Gaul and founding the Visigothic Kingdom there",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "e4d4873d-f83a-4e68-845d-446cf7d1d58e",
                     "text": "Mark, J. J.",
                     "page": "Visigoth",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2019",
                        "month": "09",
                        "day": "16"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": [
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "410",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  }
               ],
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": "."
            },
            {
               "text": "After establishing a presence in Gaul, the Visigoths continued their expansion into the Iberian Peninsula around <htdate0>. By <htdate1>, they controlled the region shown in green on the map in this section",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "4588cb01-66e8-45e8-84a4-49fc4de02c9b",
                     "text": "<i>Atlas Nacional de España</i>",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "e4d4873d-f83a-4e68-845d-446cf7d1d58e",
                     "text": "Mark, J. J.",
                     "page": "Visigoth",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2019",
                        "month": "09",
                        "day": "16"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "9ac63913-6a20-4680-bebf-51ff99a4bb31",
                     "text": "Britannica, The Editors of Encyclopaedia",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": [
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "415",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  },
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "624",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  }
               ],
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": "."
            },
            {
               "text": "The Visigothic kingdom ultimately fell in <htdate0>. Although traditionally described as a Muslim \"invasion\", contemporary analysis suggests a more complex situation. The councils held in Visigothic territory reveal significant oppression toward women, Jews, and Arian Christians, leading parts of the population to welcome Muslim intervention",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "82ba06a3-96ba-4e11-87dd-f200977c6931",
                     "text": "Montero, Pedro",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "1861",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "cd1a4bed-9754-4888-aee9-559d59503860",
                     "text": "Haines, Charles R.",
                     "page": "pp. 12",
